    "description": "Odawara Auto-Machine Mfg. Co., Ltd. designs, manufactures, sells, and maintains fare collection equipment for route buses and one-man railway vehicles in Japan. It operates through the Fare Collection Equipment Business and System Development segments. The company offers fare boxes, fare box safes, fare box software, ticket issuing machines, card equipment, LCD fare displays, and voice synthesizers, settlement device, data management server, software, as well as contactless IC card systems; software for card devices; multi-payment terminal; and tablet terminal. It also engages in development, engineering, software design, and import/export sales of systems and equipment for transportation infrastructure projects, ETC-related development projects, and other social infrastructure projects; product maintenance services; and sales and maintenance services for equipment, transportation infrastructure projects and ETC-related projects. In addition, the company offers departure signs and various indicators for railways, as well as display and guidance devices for airports. Further, it engages in system development, engineering, software design, and import/export sale of systems and equipment. Further, it is involved in product repairs and specification changes, and selling of maintenance parts. The company serves bus operators, railway companies, and local governments. It sells its products through sales offices and sales agents. Odawara Auto-Machine Mfg. Co., Ltd. was founded in 1950 and is headquartered in Odawara, Japan."
